	<h3>1. Tilt v.s. Target - Setting your funding goal</h3>
	<hr>
	<center><img src="/assets/over_funded.png"></center>
	<blockquote>	
	  <p>At <a href="https://crowdtilt.com">Crowdtilt</a> (the creators of Crowdhoster) we like to stress "tilt v.s. target" when helping campaigns set goals.</p><br>
	  <ul>
	  	<li>The "tilt" is our own language for "campaign funding goal." It's the number that you type in as your Crowdhoster goal when setting up the campaign. (For example, a campaign for a color changing iPhone case could have a "tilt" goal of $2,500).</li><br>
	  	<li>The "target" is a funding amount above your published "tilt" goal that would allow you increase the quality of the product, trip, or experience that you're raising money for. Think of this as a "stretch goal."</li>
	  </ul>
	</blockquote>
	<blockquote>
	  <p>How should you implement a "tilt" goal and "target" goal in your campaign?</p><br>
	  <ul>
